' ---
' artifact-id: b-usecase-vs002-v1
' artifact-type: diagram
' name: "Value Stream: Brownfield Onboarding — Use Case View"
' diagram-type: usecase
' version: 0.1.0
' status: draft
' phase-produced: B
' owner-agent: SA
' engagement: ENG-001
' domain: core-platform
' purpose: >
'   Stakeholder-facing view of VS-002 (Brownfield Onboarding): the five stages
'   through which the SDLC multi-agent system delivers value to a user who brings
'   an existing target system into the framework. Covers entry at EP-G: reverse
'   architecture, gap assessment, model confirmation, and governance activation.
'   Intended audience: PO, user / engagement owner, Architecture Board.
' entity-ids-used:
'   - VS-002
'   - ACT-001
'   - BCO-001
'   - BSV-001
'   - BSV-002
'   - BSV-003
'   - BSV-004
'   - BSV-005
'   - BSV-009
' ---
@startuml b-usecase-vs002-v1
!include ../_macros.puml
!include ../_archimate-stereotypes.puml

left to right direction
skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor #F0F4FE
  BorderColor #4682B4
  ArrowColor #4682B4
  ActorBorderColor #B8860B
  ActorBackgroundColor #FEFDF0
}
skinparam usecaseBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam padding 10

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Actors
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
actor "User\n(Engagement Owner)" as ACT_001_uc
actor "Architecture Board\n(BCO-001)" as BCO_001_uc

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VS-002: Brownfield Onboarding — five stages as use cases
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
rectangle "VS-002: Brownfield Onboarding  [Entry: EP-G]" {

  usecase "**Stage 1**\nSystem Discovery\n──────────────\nBSV-002 App & Tech Architecture\nBSV-005 Requirements Mgmt\n(inferred entity inventory)" as S1
  usecase "**Stage 2**\nArchitecture Reconstruction\n──────────────\nBSV-001 Business Architecture\nBSV-002 App & Tech Architecture\n(all layers reconstructed)" as S2
  usecase "**Stage 3**\nGap & Risk Assessment\n──────────────\nBSV-001 Business Architecture\nBSV-004 Safety Governance\n(risk-annotated gap list)" as S3
  usecase "**Stage 4**\nModel Confirmation\n──────────────\nBSV-009 User Decisions\nBSV-005 Requirements Mgmt\n(user validates inferences)" as S4
  usecase "**Stage 5**\nGovernance Activation\n──────────────\nBSV-003 Project Coordination\nBSV-004 Safety Governance\n(Phase G live)" as S5

}

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Relationships
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' User drives the brownfield entry and participates in all stages
ACT_001_uc --> S1 : triggers\n(provides target repo)
ACT_001_uc --> S2 : receives\nreconstructed model
ACT_001_uc --> S3 : receives\ngap assessment
ACT_001_uc --> S4 : validates\ninferred entities
ACT_001_uc --> S5 : receives\ngovernance baseline

' Architecture Board is the authority for governance activation
BCO_001_uc --> S5 : activates\nPhase G governance

' Sequential flow
S1 .> S2 : <<include>>
S2 .> S3 : <<include>>
S3 .> S4 : <<include>>
S4 .> S5 : <<include>>

note bottom of S4
  Stage 4 may iterate: user submits corrections,
  model is updated, re-confirmed until no open CQs.
  Governed by BEV-004 (Clarification Raised) loop.
end note

note bottom of S5
  Stage 5 completion fires BEV-008 (Engagement Completed).
  After activation, change management runs as
  ongoing Phase G — no further VS-002 stages.
end note

@enduml
